message: /* Definition of genocide */ added reference to [[Democide]] to address any perceived shortcomings of [[Genocide]] as it relates to political killings being omitted from the original (and current) definition of Genocide.
The link was redundantly cited again in plain text.

Previous entry listed John Mackey as strongly "anti-union", but cited no sources for this claim. I added that Mackey (according to sources that I actually DID cite) is neither "pro-union" nor "anti-union", but rather that he believes in a philosophy on unions that can be termed "beyond union." I cited my source as a reference for any interested reader to delve deeper on.
Removed the line, "The Progressive Era played a pivotal role in US history." This is editorializing and opinion.
This article had two "budgets" for the film listed. Cleaned up the one without the source, to make it so that it only shows the one $8.5M, which actually has a source cited. "Budget	$8.5 million[1]"

/* Current projects */ added that izzit.org has featured Scott Bakula in one of its productions, here is the link from izzit.org featuring the "celebrity" Scott Bakula from Star Trek Enterprise: https://www.izzit.org/products/detail.php?video=everyones_space

/* Silk Road, arrest, and trial */ previous edit was applied to the wrong place, moved, "but in a highly irregular move" to the correct spot, providing the reader with context as to the regularity of considering evidence into

/* Silk Road, arrest, and trial */ added context to the line about Ross Ulbricht's trial having "evidence...introduced at trial supporting the allegations." but that he was not charged in any way and was not sentenced related to the alleged "hits" as contextually framed as, "but in a highly irregular move,"
/* Struggle for publication */  corrected "Vad Yashem" to the correct "Yad Vashem"...

/* Filmography */ The film documentary "Suffer No Fools" is not in any way prefaced by "Up from the projects :" from the source cited. Thus removed this unnecessary and incorrect text, so now it should be a link to the film "Suffer No Fools" streaming directly as well as the correct title.
/* Filmography */    the prior link did NOT link to the correct film "Suffer No Fools" by Walter Williams. Now it should, if not, I'll make a minor edit to ensure it does.

/* History */  added "Canadian-" to now read "Canadian-American liberal economist" John Kenneth Galbraith. When I went back and reviewed John Kenneth Galbraith's wikipedia page, I noticed that he was actually described as "Canadian-American liberal economist" so I wanted to make sure this reference to him is being consistent then.

/* History */  removed "left leaning" and instead replaced with "American liberal economist" John Kenneth Galbraith. This is then consistent with the current description of John Kenneth Galbraith as it stands now on his wiki page.
/* External links */    added a link for Capitaf.org which is another part of the Free To Choose Network portfolio. See the link for cited reference.
/* History */    removed italics where unnecessary because they were used out of context of the title of a film.

There were parentheses around one instance of Free To Choose Network. Did not see why? So (Free To Choose Network) now reads as Free To Choose Network and is consistent with the rest of the instances.
Changed "The Network has three main initiatives" to "Free To Choose Network has three main initiatives" for inclusive grammatical description.
Removed the quotations marks around the "Free To Choose Media" first reference. Again, redundant and unnecessary.
Just unbolded "Free To Choose Network" as it appeared the second time. See no reason for it to appear as BOLD both times.

Previously this article cited the "Palmer R. Chitester Fund" as related to "Free To Choose Network", which is not the case. Citations included. Some other slight grammatical edits and edits made for ease of reading and flow, no substantive edits made.
cleaned up the flow of the how the message read, didn't change any substance..

the ClueBot undid my edit, it was not a vandalism edit, my edit is valid and was simply saying that after Bork, there was Kennedy, and THEN Judge Doug Ginsburg and only then did Kennedy get his nomination... skipping over Judge Doug Ginsburg is missing a part of history there...

/* Visit to Chile */ The picture provided did not have proper citations. Also, was taking up a large amount of space on this section of the page. Left remaining picture intact due to heightened relevance to the subject matter at hand.
